  "prompt": "To have an online shop in Hong-Kong, what payment and delivery options should I implement to cover 90% of the cases?",
  "response": "To ensure your online shop in Hong Kong covers 90% of the cases for payment and delivery options, consider implementing the following:\n\n### Payment Options:\n1. **Credit and Debit Cards**:\n   - Visa\n   - MasterCard\n   - American Express\n\n2. **Digital Wallets and Mobile Payments**:\n   - AlipayHK\n   - WeChat Pay HK\n   - PayMe (by HSBC)\n\n3. **Bank Transfers**:\n   - Direct Transfer through major banks in Hong Kong\n   - FPS (Faster Payment System) for instant bank transfers\n\n4. **PayPal**:\n   - Widely used and trusted international payment option\n\n### Delivery Options:\n1. **Local Couriers**:\n   - SF Express\n   - Hong Kong Post (Speedpost)\n   - Lalamove (for same-day delivery)\n\n2. **Pick-up Points & Lockers**:\n   - SF Express stores and lockers\n   - Hong Kong Post \"iPostal stations\"\n   - 7-Eleven stores (for MTR/Convenience Store pick-up) \n\n3. **In-store Pickup** (if you have a physical location)\n   - Allows customers to collect their orders directly from your physical shop.\n\nImplementing these payment and delivery options should cover most of the needs of online shoppers in Hong Kong, ensuring smooth transactions and efficient delivery services.",
